<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>New Recipe</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/partials/header.css">
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Karla:wght@350;400;600;700;800&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/recipe/new.css">
</head>
<body>
    <%- include("../partials/header") %> 
    <%- include("../partials/flash") %> 
    <main>
        <div class="container-main">
            <a class="link" href="/recipes">Back</a>
            <div class="form-container">
                <h1>Share a Recipe!</h1>
                <form action="/recipes/new" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                    <div class="form-item">
                        <label for="title">Recipe Name:</label>
                        <input id="title" type="text" name ="recipe[title]" placeholder="ex. Egg Sandwich" autocorrect="off" autocomplete="off" required >
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-item">
                        <label for="img">Image:</label>
                        <!-- <input id="img" type="img" name="recipe[image]" placeholder="img.com/1235.png" autocomplete="off" required > -->
                        <input type="file" name="image" id="img" required>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-item">
                        <label for="ingredients">Ingredients:</label>
                        <textarea name="recipe[ingredients]" id="ingredients" cols="30" rows="10" placeholder="4 LargeEggs&#x0a;4 English Muffins&#x0a;Medium Avocado, sliced into 8 wedges&#x0a;4 Slices cheddar cheese" required></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-item">
                        <label for="body">Directions:</label>
                        <textarea id="body" name="recipe[body]" cols="75" rows="20" autocomplete="off" placeholder="1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F, and use cooking oil to lightly grease 4 wells in a muffin tin. Crack 1 egg into each muffin cup. Bake the eggs for 15-20 minutes. &#x0a;&#x0a;2. While the eggs are cooling, slice the English muffins in half. Toast them in a toaster oven. If you donâ€™t have a toaster oven, toast muffins in a non-stick pan over medium heat until both sides are crispy. Set muffins aside.&#x0a;&#x0a;3. Build your sandwich by topping one slice of English muffin with 1 egg, 2 avocado wedges and 1 slice of cheese. Place top on English muffin. If you prefer, you can warm the sandwich in the microwave for 20 seconds to melt the cheese." onkeydown="if(event.keyCode===9){var v=this.value,s=this.selectionStart,e=this.selectionEnd;this.value=v.substring(0, s)+'\t'+v.substring(e);this.selectionStart=this.selectionEnd=s+1;return false;}" required></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <button>Post</button>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
</body>
</html>